        <prj:name>Science Goal</prj:name>
        <prj:note>The primary science is to attempt to detect, for the first time, the HD molecule in a warm bright ensed galaxy at z = 5.6. A very accurate CO velocity is already known from CO observations with ALMA. The detection of HD in a galaxy with a known large amount of molecular hydrogen will provide an important first step towards opening a new way of studying shocked molecular gas in hi-z systems. We plan to have enough S/N to measure not just a dection but also the profile shape and compare this in detail to the CO spectra take by another group. </prj:note>
